 Review comment:
   Like above, the `<<` operator is also locale-dependent by default.
   
   One way to avoid this is to call the [imbue](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/ios_base/imbue) method to change to the C locale, for example `stream.imbue(std::locale::classic())`. Also note this isn't very fast.


